quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  7,181,"And of those whom We have created, there is a community who guides (others) with the truth, and establishes justice therewith."
  7,182,"Those who reject Our Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.), We shall gradually seize them with punishment in ways they perceive not."
  7,183,"And I respite them; certainly My Plan is strong."
  9,85,"And let not their wealth or their children amaze you. Allâh’s Plan is to punish them with these things in this world, and that their souls shall depart (die) while they are disbelievers."
  9,86,"And when a Sûrah (chapter from the Qur’ân) is revealed, enjoining them to believe in Allâh and to strive hard and fight along with His Messenger, the wealthy among them ask your leave to exempt them (from Jihâd) and say, "
  9,87,"They are content to be with those (the women) who sit behind (at home). Their hearts are sealed up (from all kinds of goodness and right guidance), so they understand not."
  10,43,"And among them are some who look at you, but can you guide the blind - even though they see not?"
  10,44,"Truly! Allâh wrongs not mankind in aught; but mankind wrong themselves."
  10,45,"And on the Day when He shall gather (resurrect) them together, (it will be) as if they had not stayed (in the life of this world and graves) but an hour of a day. They will recognise each other. Ruined indeed will be those who denied the Meeting with Allâh, and were not guided."
  11,10,"But if We let him taste good (favour) after evil (poverty and harm) has touched him, he is sure to say: "
  11,11,"Except those who show patience and do righteous good deeds: those, theirs will be forgiveness and a great reward (Paradise)."
  11,12,"So perchance you (Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم) may give up a part of what is revealed unto you, and that your breast feels straitened for it because they say, "